  "commentary": "With SPX at 6603.96 sitting just below the GEX flip at 6609 and near the massive +58.3B gamma wall at 6605, dealers are currently in sell-rally mode and will aggressively hedge any upside momentum by selling futures. The PIN regime with 151.9B total GEX creates a strong magnetic pull toward the 6605 max gamma strike, while the surge in GEX (28.9% 1-min, 56.3% 5-min) indicates rapidly building hedging pressure that should cap volatility and contain price swings. Key levels: 6605 acts as resistance where dealer selling intensifies, 6609 flip level determines regime change, and 6590 negative gamma provides downside support where dealers would buy dips.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pinned around 6605 with limited upside as dealers sell any rallies.",
